dublin_core.dcvalue: Thrombolytic treatment substantially reduces mortality and morbidity in acute myocardial infarction This survival benefit rapidly declines when thrombolysis is delayed In our department this delay has previously been measured to be 40 10 360 minutes It is important to reduce this time loss
